-- Merrill's Americas wealth management president leaving
-- 
-- Fri Jan 4, 2008 4:11pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/04/us-merrilllynch-gardner-idUSWEN323920080104

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Merrill Lynch & Co Inc's MER.N president of wealth management in the Americas will leave the brokerage at the end of the month, the company said on Friday. 

 Mac Gardner, who also was chairman of the company's industrial bank, joined Merrill Lynch in 1983 as an investment banking analyst. In a memo to employees, no reason was given for Gardner's departure. (Reporting by  Tim McLaughlin )